Key Match Events: Travis Head smashed 80 off 25 balls in the series opener.
Josh Inglis scored a century to propel Australia to 196/4 in 20 overs.
Marcus Stoinis took 4/23 for Australia, wrapping up Scotland for 126 in 16.4 overs.
Post-Match Reflections: George Munsey top scored for Scotland with 28.
Sean Abbott was the pick of the Australian bowlers with three for 39.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Scotland came close to shocking the Aussies in the T20 World Cup in June.
The series is in the bag for Australia with a match still to go.
Others: Chasing 197, Scotland were bowled out for 126 in 16.4 overs.
Jake Fraser-McGurk fell to a three-ball duck for Scotland.
The required rate touched 10 before the start of the run chase, making it challenging for Scotland.
